Currently writing some specs for a linter package and running into grammar miss-match issues:

``` js
describe('checks sloppy.html and', () => {
    let editor = null;
    beforeEach(() => {
      waitsForPromise(() => {
        return atom.workspace.open('./files/sloppy.html').then(openEditor => {
          editor = openEditor;
          console.log(editor.getGrammar().scopeName);
        });
      });
    });
});
```

The `console.log` returns:

```
text.plain.null-grammar
```

Instead of: 

```
text.html.basic
```
